## Acceptance checklist (verify all before considering this done)

- [ ] `tracker.js` works standalone on a plain HTML page with no build step
- [ ] Events batch client-side and flush on interval, size threshold, and unload
- [ ] `sendBeacon` used specifically for the unload flush path
- [ ] Server stamps authoritative timestamp; client timestamp stored separately
- [ ] Events are validated server-side against an allowlist/schema, not trusted blindly
- [ ] Sessions are computed via aggregation, not a separately-maintained collection (or the decision to denormalize is explicitly justified)
- [ ] Compound indexes exist for the session-journey and heatmap query patterns
- [ ] Sessions view supports pagination and shows event counts
- [ ] Clicking a session shows the full ordered event journey
- [ ] Heatmap view has a page selector and scales coordinates by viewport
- [ ] CORS allowlists specific origins, not `*`
- [ ] Rate limiting present on the ingestion endpoint
- [ ] `docker-compose up` brings up the full stack locally in one command
- [ ] Deployed and publicly reachable (frontend + backend + Atlas)
- [ ] README covers setup, stack, architecture, API docs, and trade-offs honestly

